plot: An old friend of Baird's is running for Mayor of a small New Hampshire town and finds himself embroiled in a scandal in the form of a missing intern and a literal contract with the Devil. Baird soon finds herself in a battle not only for her own soul, but also for the souls of all the Librarians.

While Baird is away visiting a friend, the clipping book alerts them to the death of a woman in a small town. When they get there they learn she was working for a mayoral candidate. They run into Baird who says she's here to see her friend, the other man running for mayor. They learn the woman may have learned something about the man she's working for and may have been silenced. They also discover that this may not be the first time something magical has happened in this town.—rcs0411@yahoo.com
